There have been quite a lot of updates upstream since the last pull from there. 

- What would be good to have in the context of enabling warnings such as `-Wsuggest-override` (https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/16710) is their C++11 changes: https://github.com/google/leveldb/commit/28e6d23
- There's also  #20 which was fixed in https://github.com/google/leveldb/commit/594cc987af2e0af6417c4ac2b947ee8cdad59e5e

But I'm sure there's other changes that make sense for us in the mean time 

- version 1.20 (a53934a3ae1244679f812d998a4f16f2c7f309a6) was the last merged upstream, #1 in 2017
- it's now at 1.22 (78b39d68c15ba020c0d60a3906fb66dbf1697595) + quite a few unreleased commits)

